title: RollingStones-Truth&Lies.2003-SWESUB
description:
Biography, Music History 2003



In the decades after taking London&#039;s Marquee Club by storm back in 1962, The Rolling Stones have established themselves as one of the most enduring acts in rock-and-roll history. Now, after decades of success and controversy, the critics, contemporaries, and fans of The Rolling Stones discuss the music, scandals, and excesses that made rock and roll history. With news footage and interviews spanning over forty years and twenty-four albums, this fascinating look at the legendary rock outfit covers everything from the band&#039;s inception on 1961 to their 2002 Forty Licks tour. ~ Jason Buchanan, All Movie Guide
